✅ One-Line Difference
Switch: Connects devices within the same network using MAC addresses.
Router: Connects different networks using IP addresses.
✅ Ultra-Short (Very Common in Interviews)
Switch = Inside network
Router = Between networks / Internet
✅ Router vs Switch vs Hub (One-Line Each)
Hub: Sends data to all devices (no intelligence).
Switch: Sends data to the correct device in a LAN.
Router: Sends data to the correct network (LAN ↔ Internet).
